5. Interpretation Principles
	‚Ä¢	Growth is non-linear. Movement between stages is seasonal; stress may regress axes temporarily.
	‚Ä¢	Strength ‚â† maturity. A learner may excel in an axis technically but lack moral integration (Wisdom stage).
	‚Ä¢	Axes interact. When one matures, others often follow (e.g., deeper Reflection enriches Application).
	‚Ä¢	Celebrate awareness. Stage 2 is already progress; curiosity is conversion.
	‚Ä¢	End every session with hope. ‚ÄúYou‚Äôre learning to steer, not to fit a type.‚Äù
