B. The 8 Macro-Family Descriptions
Used for the "Your Macro-Family" section of the report.
1. Root-Seekers (A-R)
	‚Ä¢	Tagline: Hold the roots; grow toward light.
	‚Ä¢	Description: Root-Seekers are custodians of continuity. They learn through depth before breadth‚Äîasking where something began and what principle sustains it. They distrust novelty unmoored from essence and often feel responsible for guarding the moral or intellectual foundations of a community. When mature, they translate heritage into guidance; when immature, they risk rigidity or nostalgia.
	‚Ä¢	Core Virtue: Fidelity ‚Äî loyalty to truth across changing contexts.
	‚Ä¢	Inner Question: ‚ÄúWhat endures beneath the surface?‚Äù
2. Integrators (A-C)
	‚Ä¢	Tagline: Connection creates comprehension.
	‚Ä¢	Description: Integrators are bridge-builders. They perceive relationships faster than boundaries and instinctively seek harmony between people, ideas, and systems. Learning for them is social: truth emerges in conversation and cooperation. They create the atmosphere in which understanding can flourish. When mature, they reconcile opposites; when immature, they blur them.
	‚Ä¢	Core Virtue: Harmony ‚Äî holding difference together in creative tension.
	‚Ä¢	Inner Question: ‚ÄúHow can we bring these parts into one living whole?‚Äù
3. Analyst-Builders (N-R)
	‚Ä¢	Tagline: Blueprints that stand the test of time.
	‚Ä¢	Description: Analyst-Builders construct the frameworks that make meaning durable. They delight in systems, measurement, and logical coherence. For them, order is beauty. They turn abstractions into functioning structures‚Äîcurricula, organizations, or machines‚Äîthat others can trust. When mature, they design with humility; when immature, they idolize control.
	‚Ä¢	Core Virtue: Order ‚Äî bringing stability through understanding.
	‚Ä¢	Inner Question: ‚ÄúHow do the parts fit so that truth can operate reliably?‚Äù
4. Contextual Innovators (N-C)
	‚Ä¢	Tagline: Relevance without compromise.
	‚Ä¢	Description: Contextual Innovators are translators of truth for their own generation. They read environments quickly and adapt ideas to meet new realities. Change excites them because it reveals fresh possibilities. They live at the frontier between heritage and innovation. When mature, they reform without rebellion; when immature, they chase novelty for its own sake.
	‚Ä¢	Core Virtue: Creativity ‚Äî renewing the familiar through imagination.
	‚Ä¢	Inner Question: ‚ÄúHow must truth look to speak meaningfully now?‚Äù
5. Visionary Connectors (Complex: e.g., A-R/C-E-D-M-H-L)
	‚Ä¢	Tagline: Speak light into possibility.
	‚Ä¢	Description: Visionary Connectors are storytellers of transformation. They sense potential in people and situations and use language, art, or leadership to awaken it. They learn best through dialogue charged with purpose and emotion. Their presence motivates others to act. When mature, they become catalytic mentors; when immature, they inspire without follow-through.
	‚Ä¢	Core Virtue: Inspiration ‚Äî awakening hope and courage in others.
6. Reflective Strategists (Complex: e.g., N-C/R-I-P-S-H-R)
	‚Ä¢	Tagline: Order in thought, grace in time.
	‚Ä¢	Description: Reflective Strategists unite contemplation with planning. They analyse causes, anticipate consequences, and move with deliberate timing. Their learning style is cyclic: observe, reflect, plan, execute, review. When mature, they become wise stewards of timing; when immature, they stall in over-analysis.
	‚Ä¢	Core Virtue: Prudence ‚Äî choosing the right action at the right moment.
7. Collaborative Creators (Complex: e.g., A-C-E-D/P-M-H-L/R)
	‚Ä¢	Tagline: We grow by growing others.
	‚Ä¢	Description: Collaborative Creators believe knowledge blossoms in community. They are energised by teamwork, shared learning, and service. Their classrooms, studios, and workplaces hum with inclusion and laughter. They translate wisdom into belonging. When mature, they create transformative teams; when immature, they avoid conflict.
	‚Ä¢	Core Virtue: Generosity ‚Äî giving time, skill, and encouragement freely.
8. Principled Pioneers (Complex: e.g., N-R-E/I-D/P-S-T-R)
	‚Ä¢	Tagline: Courage anchored in conviction.
	‚Ä¢	Description: Principled Pioneers combine integrity with initiative. They question assumptions, defend conscience, and blaze trails where truth demands new expression. Their learning is forged in struggle‚Äîthey grow by standing firm. When mature, they model moral leadership; when immature, they isolate themselves in certainty.
	‚Ä¢	Core Virtue: Courage ‚Äî acting on conviction despite resistance.
C. The 14 Axis-Card Microtexts
Used to auto-assemble the detailed "Personal Report."
	‚Ä¢	PERCEP_Assoc (A): You perceive through patterns, story, and atmosphere. Meaning arises first in intuition and relationship. You absorb whole pictures, sensing emotional truth before logic. Your challenge is to test instinct with evidence so imagination matures into insight grounded in reality.
	‚Ä¢	PERCEP_Anal (N): You perceive through definition, precision, and proof. Structure and data clarify your world. You dissect complexity until each part makes sense. Your challenge is to trust intuition sooner‚Äîallow discovery to precede verification so analysis serves creativity rather than replaces it.
	‚Ä¢	INTERP_Root (R): You seek the essence behind appearances. Origins and causes fascinate you; tradition feels like a moral compass. You learn by asking why. Growth comes when you let context reshape application so ancient truth continues to breathe in the present.
	‚Ä¢	INTERP_Context (C): You see truth as situational and dynamic. Application across environments matters more than origin. You learn by asking how and where. Growth comes when you tether adaptability to enduring principles so relevance doesn‚Äôt become relativism.
	‚Ä¢	REFLEC_Internal (I): Understanding deepens in solitude. You digest before you speak, and insight feels sacred until expressed. Silence organises your thoughts into coherence. Growth comes by sharing drafts of ideas earlier‚Äîdialogue turns private wisdom into communal growth.
	‚Ä¢	REFLEC_External (E): Understanding crystallises in communication. Talking, teaching, or debating reveals what you know. Interaction brings clarity. Growth comes by practising stillness so expression draws from depth, not momentum.
	‚Ä¢	APPLIC_Ideal (D): You move through vision and meaning. Purpose fuels persistence; projects must matter morally. You reform systems to reflect conscience. Growth comes by mastering logistics‚Äîlet procedure protect passion so ideals endure beyond inspiration.
	‚Ä¢	APPLIC_Prag (P): You move through method and precision. Order brings peace; outcomes prove worth. You build reliability around purpose. Growth comes by re-igniting imagination‚Äîlet meaning steer efficiency so progress remains human.
	‚Ä¢	MOTIV_Self (S): Autonomy drives you. You set internal standards and measure success by integrity. Independence keeps your learning alive. Growth comes by embracing partnership‚Äîcollaboration multiplies personal excellence into collective transformation.
	‚Ä¢	MOTIV_Mutual (M): Belonging drives you. Shared purpose sustains effort. You flourish where contribution meets connection. Growth comes by strengthening individual conviction‚Äîserve from strength, not compliance, so empathy retains direction.
	‚Ä¢	ORIENT_Temp (T): You live in milestones and measurable progress. Deadlines energise focus; rhythm breeds trust. You master time through sequence. Growth comes by widening perspective‚Äîlift your eyes from the clock to the horizon so pace gains purpose.
	‚Ä¢	ORIENT_Holist (H): You live in seasons and synthesis. Perspective precedes detail; meaning shapes rhythm. You master time through story. Growth comes by narrowing focus‚Äîtranslate vision into immediate steps so depth becomes delivery.
	‚Ä¢	VALUE_Love (L): You lead through empathy and restoration. People feel safe and seen in your presence. Compassion is your first instinct. Growth comes by pairing tenderness with courage‚Äîboundaries protect the very love that inspires them.
	‚Ä¢	VALUE_Respect (R): You lead through fairness and consistency. People trust your reliability and justice. Integrity is your language of care. Growth comes by tempering principle with warmth‚Äîmercy completes the truth you guard.
